<br>
But we still had the one computer issue so we couldn't play together and finally got to the point we were fighting over who could play when so we got another pc and a new copy of the game....meanwhile his friends had changed servers so I was left on emarr alone =(  <br>
<br>
By January 2000 he was tired of server hopping with the other guild and we made Ghie and Ghia cause I told him I would play with him starting new if he wanted to come back to emarr to play with me.  We played them together for a long time til the reality that I just didn't really like being a warrior (ghia) was too much for me.  I played Evelle got her up to the point she could play with Ghie.  We have been in mostly the same guilds since then.  <br>
<br>
We have fun but it wouldn't be as fun without him.   <p>

Evelle Dark Priestess of Inny

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uulujainebonelphette.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulujain Ebonelphette</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_cyanspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1395<br> <font color=#E9D756>(8/3/02 12:17:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10255.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Interesting.</span><hr size=1> Funny thing is, when I first met Celoria, 3D games made her sick. She couldn't really handle watching me play Descent 3 or Quake 2 or Half-Life etc. Yet, here she is, playing away in hardware accelerated fairy land <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
